<item>
            <title>[LU-1585] Incorrect timestamp calculation in lst stat command</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1585</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;During the patch review for fix &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,3192&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,3192&lt;/a&gt; (Jira ticket &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-445&quot; title=&quot;Send timestamps with LNet counters&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-445&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-445&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), it was found that the timestamp delta done in the routine let_timeval_diff() (file: lst.c) has a bug.  This delta is used to determine the bandwidth reported with the &quot;let stat&quot; command.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This ticket has been opened to track back-porting the fix to this routine to previous affected releases.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
